                            <comment id="14697162" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 14 Aug 2015 14:58:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1695928 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/1.8&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1695928&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1695928&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2935&quot; title=&quot;Problem while extracting font from PDFontSetting (used in PDExtendedGraphicsState)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2935&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2935&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: /Font array member 0 is an indirect object in ExtGState dict&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14697181" author="tilman" created="Fri, 14 Aug 2015 15:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report. According to the specification, this MUST be an indirect object, thus there should have been a wrong rendering long ago already. So either we have ignored that item, or there is no file &quot;in the wild&quot; that uses this feature. If you have one and can share it, we&apos;d be interested.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14699132" author="exerus94" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 07:47:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please take a look at this file :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/veraPDF/veraPDF-corpus/blob/master/PDF_A-1b/6.1%20File%20structure/6.1.12%20Implementation%20limits/veraPDF%20test%20suite%206-1-12-t02-fail-b.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/veraPDF/veraPDF-corpus/blob/master/PDF_A-1b/6.1%20File%20structure/6.1.12%20Implementation%20limits/veraPDF%20test%20suite%206-1-12-t02-fail-b.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14699133" author="exerus94" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 07:47:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added example file&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14699734" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 16:00:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1696310 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/1.8&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1696310&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1696310&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2935&quot; title=&quot;Problem while extracting font from PDFontSetting (used in PDExtendedGraphicsState)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2935&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2935&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: use default font if no font is set&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14699735" author="tilman" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 16:01:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks. I tried to render that file with the pre-fix version, there&apos;s a warning and a default font is used. For 1.8, an NPE would be thrown. So I&apos;ve added a fix we have in the 2.0 version to avoid the NPE in 1.8 as well. The NPE in 1.8 strengthens my opinion that this PDF feature is not used in the wild.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14699740" author="tilman" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 16:07:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The next problem to fix is that this veraPDF test case isn&apos;t handled properly in preflight. This will be done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2804&quot; title=&quot;Validate PDF/A-1b files of veraPDF project&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2804&quot;&gt;PDFBOX-2804&lt;/a&gt;. Again, thanks for your contribution!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
